I"”<p>The title is wrong, at least technically. Itâ€™s not about sending mails from an alias, but rather from a shared mailbox.
If you want to send mails from another sender address then your primary mailbox address, itâ€™s possible to create a shared mailbox and allow yourself to send in its name.</p>

<p>To create a shared mailbox, login to the <a href="https://outlook.office.com/ecp/"><em>Exchange Admin Center</em> (<strong>ECP</strong>)</a>.
Navigate to <code class="highlighter-rouge">recipients</code> &gt; <code class="highlighter-rouge">shared</code> and create a <strong>new shared mailbox</strong>:</p>

<ul>
  <li><em>Display name:</em> <code class="highlighter-rouge">whatever...</code></li>
  <li><em>Email address:</em> <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;$SENDER_ADDRESS&gt;</code></li>
  <li><em>Users:</em> add your mailbox to the list of authorized senders (<strong>+</strong>)</li>
</ul>

